<div id="pf29" class="pf w6 hb" data-page-no="29"><div class="pc pc29 w6 hb"><div class="t m538 x28 h2d y61a ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 5 July 27 to August 2 </div><div class="t m538 x1c h2e y61b ff7 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m539 x63 h2f y61c ff1 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ihe2 Thrird 1115milam </div><div class="t m539 xd1 h2e y61b ff7 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"><span class="fc0 sc0"> </span><span class="_ _0"> </span><span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m539 x1c h2e y61d ff7 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> <span class="_ _1"> </span><span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m3fc x13 h30 y39d ff3 fs1a fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[1112 </div><div class="t m3fc x1c h2e y61e ff7 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> <span class="_ _2"> </span><span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m3fc x1c h2e y61f ff7 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"><span class="fc0 sc0"> </span><span class="_ _2"> </span><span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m3fc x1c h2e y620 ff7 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"><span class="fc0 sc0"> </span><span class="_ _3"> </span><span class="fc0 sc0"> </span><span class="_ _4"> </span><span class="fc0 sc0"> </span><span class="_ _5"> </span><span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m53a x48 h2d y2c7 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The wicked tell God to leave them </div><div class="t m53b x2 h2d y621 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">alone; </div><div class="t m53c x9f h2d y2cc ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">they don&apos;t want to know his will </div><div class="t m53d x2 h2d y622 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for their lives. </div><div class="t m53e x48 h2d y2ce ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">They think there is no need to serve </div><div class="t m53f x2 h2d y623 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God </div><div class="t m540 x9f h2d y624 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nor any advantage in praying to </div><div class="t m27e x2 h2d y625 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">him. </div><div class="t m541 x48 h2d y626 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">They claim they succeed by their </div><div class="t m512 x2 h2d y627 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">own strength, </div><div class="t m542 xbb h2d y628 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">but their way of thinking I can&apos;t </div><div class="t m420 x2 h2d y629 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">accept&quot; (Job 21:14-16, TEV). </div><div class="t m543 x48 h14 y2d5 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The third dialogue or cycle, as </div><div class="t m544 x0 h14 y62a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">,understood by the author of these </div><div class="t m545 x21 h14 y2d7 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lessons, includes Job 21 through 31. </div><div class="t m474 x21 h14 y62b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">These chapters cover the following </div><div class="t m546 x21 h14 y62c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">items: </div><div class="t m4f4 x48 h14 y62d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;1. Job&apos;s first speech: he maintains </div><div class="t m547 x2 h14 y62e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that the wicked sometimes </div><div class="t m548 x2 h14 y62f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">prosper, 21:1-34. </div><div class="t m491 x53 h14 y630 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m549 x2 h14 y630 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eliphaz&apos;s speech: he urges Job </div><div class="t m54a x2 h14 y631 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to repent, 22:1-30. </div><div class="t m494 x53 h14 y632 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m268 x2 h14 y632 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s second speech: he </div><div class="t m54b x2 h14 y633 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">expresses his longing for an </div><div class="t m54c x2 h14 y75 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">opportunity to appear before </div><div class="t m54d x9f h14 y634 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">, God, 23:1 to 24:25. </div><div class="t m496 x53 h14 y635 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m54e x2 h14 y636 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bildad&apos;s speech: he asserts that </div><div class="t m54f x2 h14 y637 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">man cannot be justified before </div><div class="t m550 x2 h14 y638 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God, 25:1-6. </div><div class="t m44f x53 h14 y639 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m551 x2 h14 y639 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s third and longest speech: </div><div class="t m552 x2 h14 y63a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">he reviews his experience and </div><div class="t m27a x2 h14 y63b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">maintains his innocence, 26:1 to </div><div class="t m469 x2 h14 y63c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">31:40.&quot;â€”S.D.A. </div><div class="t m553 x33 h14 y63c ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bible </div><div class="t m554 x2 h14 y7d ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Commentary, </div><div class="t m555 xba h14 y7d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">vol. 3, pp. 496, </div><div class="t m556 x2 h14 y63d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">497. </div><div class="t m389 x32 h14 y63e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The present lesson touches certain </div><div class="t m557 x22 h14 y63f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">high points in chapters 21 through 27. </div><div class="t m558 x22 h14 y640 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Lesson 6 deals with chapter 28. </div><div class="t m17c x22 h14 y641 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lesson 1 has summarized chapters 29 </div><div class="t m48c x22 h14 y642 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">through 31.) </div><div class="t m380 x32 h14 y643 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It should be pointed out that </div><div class="t m559 x22 h14 y644 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">expositors differ on their  </div><div class="t m139 xd2 h14 y645 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reconstruction of these chapters. </div><div class="t m55a xd2 h14 y621 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Some begin in third cycle with chapter </div><div class="t m55b xd2 h14 y2cc ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">22. Some assume that Job 24:18-25 </div><div class="t m55c xd2 h14 y622 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">should be attributed to Zophar; </div><div class="t m409 xd2 h14 y3a2 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">chapter 26:5-14 to Bildad; and chapter </div><div class="t m55d xd2 h14 y623 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">27:13-23 to Zophar. Some of these </div><div class="t m555 xd2 h14 y2c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">questions cannot be answered with </div><div class="t m55e xd2 h14 y3a5 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">complete certainty, but the </div><div class="t m113 x9e h14 y3a5 ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">message </div><div class="t m55f xd2 h14 y646 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of the book is not seriously affected by</div><div class="t m560 xd2 h14 y3a7 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">these technical considerations. This </div><div class="t m53a xd2 h14 y647 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lesson follows the outline in the </div><div class="t m561 xd2 h14 y648 ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">S.D.A. Bible Commentary. </div><div class="t m562 xb0 h14 y649 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The text that has been chosen to </div><div class="t m563 xd2 h14 y64a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">introduce this lesson (Job 21:14-16) </div><div class="t m564 xd2 h14 y64b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">paints an accurate picture of </div><div class="t m1b5 xd2 h14 y64c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">humanism in every age. The secularist </div><div class="t m565 xd2 h14 y64d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">may acknowledge the possibility that </div><div class="t m566 x8e h14 y64e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God exists, but he wants to live as if </div><div class="t m567 xd2 h14 y64f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">there were no God. He is like the little </div><div class="t m568 xd2 h14 y650 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">girl who prayed, &quot;God, I wish You </div><div class="t m569 xd2 h14 y651 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">would quit following me around.&quot; He </div><div class="t m18a xd2 h14 y652 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">does not seek to be guided by God. He </div><div class="t m56a xd2 h14 y653 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sees nothing in </div><div class="t m56b x8a h2d y653 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">prayer. </div><div class="t m56c xd0 h14 y653 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">He feels all </div><div class="t m56d xd2 h14 y654 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sufficient. Job identified himself with </div><div class="t m56e xd2 h14 y655 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the faithful of all ages when he said, </div><div class="t m281 xd2 h14 y656 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Their way of thinking I can&apos;t accept&quot; </div><div class="t m56f xd2 h14 y657 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 16, TEV). </div><div class="t m127 xb0 h14 y658 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This passage also verified Job&apos;s basic </div><div class="t m570 xd2 h14 y659 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reliance upon God. In his </div><div class="t m571 x8e h14 y65a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">discouragement, he may have </div><div class="t m572 x8e h14 y65b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">complained and questioned, but his </div><div class="t m573 x8e h14 y65c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">basic loyalty was unimpaired. It is </div><div class="t m574 x8e h14 y65d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">important to distinguish in any life </div><div class="t m575 x8e h14 y65e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">between the varying moods created by </div><div class="t m535 x8e h14 y65f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">changing circumstances and the </div><div class="t m576 x8e h14 y660 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">underlying commitments that are </div><div class="t m49d x8e h14 y661 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">unaffected by the fortunes of life. </div><div class="t m152 x8e h2d y44 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">DAILY HIGHLIGHTS </div><div class="t m577 x8e h2d y662 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m578 x3c h2d y663 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Please Listen!&quot; </div><div class="t m472 x3c h2d y3c1 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 21:1-3) </div><div class="t m579 x8e h2d y664 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m57a x3c h2d y665 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Why Do Wicked Prosper? </div><div class="t m57b x3c h2d y666 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 21:7-13) </div><div class="t m57c x8e h2d y667 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m57d x3c h2d y668 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Wasted Advice </div><div class="t m57e x3c h2d y669 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 22:21-26) </div><div class="t m57f x8e h2d y66a ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m580 xd3 h2d y66a ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Reawakening of Confidence </div><div class="t m581 x3c h2d y3c7 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 23:10) </div><div class="t m57f x8e h2d y3c8 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m582 xd3 h2d y3c9 ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What Is Man Worth? </div><div class="t m583 x3c h2d y66b ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 25:6) </div><div class="t m584 x8e h2d y3cc ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m570 xd3 h2d y3cc ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A Clear Conscience </div><div class="t m472 xd3 h2d y66c ff2 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 27:1-6) </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
